        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "test: stabilize maintainer prepare baseline",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nStabilizes the local maintainer prepare baseline failures seen while preparing #85791.\n\n- updates the node-host allow-always coverage test to use a supported direct executable fixture instead of a shell-wrapped interpreter command that is now rejected by the safety boundary\n- skips the chmod cleanup retry assertion under root, where root can remove through the permission-denied fixture\n- isolates mac packaging PATH fixtures from host `/usr/bin/pnpm` / `/usr/bin/corepack`\n- makes Telegram channel-post album timer tests deterministic and fail loudly on timeout\n- increases Slack dropped-history media resolution timeout so WSL/root lanes do not miss delayed history media\n\n## Maintainer alert\n\nThis does not add config schema/options, plugin API/contract, CLI flags, env vars, migrations, or public config/plugin surface.\n\nIt does intentionally change Slack dropped-history media behavior by increasing the internal media resolution budget from 1s/3s to 10s/15s. That is not a new surface, but it is maintainer-visible channel behavior and should be accepted explicitly before merge.\n\n## Validation\n\nFrom WSL root in `/root/src/openclaw-workflow/.worktrees/baseline-prepare-gates-20260605c` at `cbf66c346b`:\n\n- `pnpm install --frozen-lockfile` -> passed\n- restored local `protobufjs@8.4.0` package payload from the published tarball because this machine's install was missing `google/protobuf/*.json`; without that local repair `pnpm build` failed before source validation\n- `env -u DISPLAY -u WAYLAND_DISPLAY OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs test/scripts/e2e-temp-state-dir.test.ts test/scripts/package-mac-app.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot.create-telegram-bot.channel-post-media.test.ts src/plugins/plugin-registry.test.ts src/node-host/invoke.test.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.test.ts --reporter=verbose --testTimeout=30000` -> passed, 5 Vitest shards in 74.26s\n- five failed prepare shard configs rerun individually with `env -u DISPLAY -u WAYLAND_DISPLAY OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config <config> --reporter=dot --testTimeout=30000` -> passed\n  - `test/vitest/vitest.tooling.config.ts`\n  - `test/vitest/vitest.extension-telegram.config.ts`\n  - `test/vitest/vitest.plugins.config.ts`\n  - `test/vitest/vitest.unit-src.config.ts`\n  - `test/vitest/vitest.extension-slack.config.ts`\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/node-host/invoke.test.ts test/scripts/e2e-temp-state-dir.test.ts test/scripts/package-mac-app.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot.create-telegram-bot.channel-post-media.test.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.ts` -> passed\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json src/node-host/invoke.test.ts test/scripts/e2e-temp-state-dir.test.ts test/scripts/package-mac-app.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot.create-telegram-bot.channel-post-media.test.ts extensions/slack/src/monitor/message-handler/prepare.ts` -> 0 warnings, 0 errors\n- `git diff --check` -> passed\n- `env -u DISPLAY -u WAYLAND_DISPLAY OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 pnpm build` -> passed\n- `env -u DISPLAY -u WAYLAND_DISPLAY OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 pnpm check` -> passed\n- `env -u DISPLAY -u WAYLAND_DISPLAY pnpm test` -> passed, 88 Vitest shards in 1197.64s\n\nNo merge performed.\r\n",
